Tap 'n' Play Technologies - FFA & A-League Trading Cards 2015-2016

2015-16

FFA & A-League Trading Cards 2015-2016

Tap 'n' Play Technologies

Australia

267 cards

Football Federation Australia and Professional Footballers Australia finally signed their Collective Bargaining Agreement on Friday (6 November, 2015) which releases Tap'N'Play to commence manufacture of the 2015/16 FFA & A-League Trading Card collection.

All designs are approved so we are immediatley ready to place them into manufacture. Production will commence on Monday (9 November) and will take approximately 4 weeks so it's likely that an early December release date will be announced soon. The cards will be available through online card sellers, newsagents, 7/11 stores and Coles Express stores in Australia and New Zealand. Only 150 cases available.

The Archie Thompson Match Worn Jersey Signature cards will be available via Redemption Cards in packs. The jersey swatches in this card are from Archie's 2015 Hyundai A-League Grand Final Jersey, where the Melbourne Victory side defeated Sydney FC 3-0 at AAMI Park on 17 May.

Holly & Benji is the European version of a Japanese comic book series called Captain Tsubasa. The original comic book series appeared in 1981 and was soon followed by a TV cartoon series.

Fans of Serie A may have seen advert appearing around the grounds of some matches recently. Italian newspapers Corriere dello Sport-Stadio and Tuttosport newspapers have provided Holly & Benji figures for fans to collect. Each one measures 12.5cm, comes in it's own box and costs €10,90 when buying a copy of one of the newspapers.
